        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:28PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 325 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Kirkland, or 6 miles east of Childress, moving
east at 35 mph. An addition strong thunderstorm was located on the
north side of Childress, also moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Childress and Kirkland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
